Secondary Store Type - (Choose all that apply) 
Note: The store does not have to be “Other” for the primary store type to have a secondary type, and not all stores (including “Other” stores) will have a secondary store type. Select Not Applicable option instead of leaving blank if not applicable.  

 

Definitions:

Corner Store - A small-scale store that sells a limited selection of foods and other products. We will use the definition of a corner store as defined by The Food Trust: 

1) Less than 1000 sq feet

2) Less than 4 aisles

3) 1 cash register (often)

4) Food is primary product

B. Availability 

2. Shelf space  -  Proportion of Reduced-fat dinners / regular dinners

 
Estimate the proportion of the reduced-fat compared to regular frozen dinners only for Stouffer’s® or the alternate brand selected and mark either ≤ 10%, 11-33%, 34-50%, or 51%+. If there is only a reduced-fat option of a particular brand and not a regular version (e.g., Healthy Choice), estimate the proportion of the reduced-fat dinners compared to the regular across all brands.



Remember that Lean Cuisine is part of the Stouffer's brand. 


	
		
			
			For example:

			
				Lean Cuisine Reduced-fat dinners = 1 column
				Stouffer's regular dinners  = 10 columns
				1 column / 10 columns = 10% 
				so Lean Cuisine Reduced-fat dinners / Stouffer's regular dinners = 10%
			

			Remember:

			
				Reduced-fat frozen dinner = ≤ 9 g fat/serving (8-11 oz. package)
				Regular frozen dinner = ≥ 10 g fat/serving (8-11 oz. package)
